Ingest More Data into Data Cloud with New Third-Party Connectors (Beta)

Import data from a growing list of external databases and applications into Data Cloud for harmonization. You can now ingest data from Adobe Analytics, Apache Hive, Asana, Azure Cosmos DB, eBay Analytics, Google Contacts, Google Drive, Google Spanner, GraphQL, IBM Cloud Object Storage, IBM Informix, Microsoft Dynamics 365, Oracle Eloqua, PayPal, SendGrid, Snapchat Ads, Spark SQL, and SugarCRM.

Where: This change applies to Data Cloud in Developer, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions.

When: This feature is available starting in July 2024.

How: In Data Cloud Setup, under Connectors, create a connection using the new Beta connector. Then in Data Streams, select the connection as your source.
title: Ingesting External Data with New Third-Party Connectors
